-- Beijing Accepts Proposal for Electoral Reforms in Hong Kong, SCMP Reports
-- Frederik Balfour
-- 2010-06-20T02:58:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-20/beijing-accepts-proposal-for-electoral-reforms-in-hong-kong-scmp-reports.html

          
          
             The Hong Kong government will
announce tomorrow it has accepted a proposal on electoral
reforms in Hong Kong, the South China Morning Post reported
today, citing lawmakers.  
 The government has received approval from Beijing to accept
the deal put forward by the Democratic Party to amend a package
of reforms on how members of the Legislative Council shall be
elected in 2012, according to legislator Ronny
Tong Ka-wah and others who received the message from mainland
contacts, the paper said.  
